  "texts": [
    "LSTM [63] is the type of RNN that solves the vanishing gradient problem through the gated structure that can retain long-term dependencies between the input data by shifting the relevant information down the chain of sequences to make predictions.",
    "In LSTM cells, the flow of information is controlled through input, forget, and output gates, in combination with the activation functions.",
    "The input gate decides which information is needed during the current step.",
    "An input layer represents the features at a given Time (t) and has the same dimensional size as that of the feature size.",
    "The forget gate determines the necessary information that needs to be kept from previous steps."
  ],
